{"article_id":"DVxDZS9oOS2XOjET","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Trump administration told a federal judge late Friday","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"that it won ' t defend the legality of the Obama-era DACA amnesty","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"- but said","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"the court should be wary of cutting it off entirely ,","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"as states such as Texas have requested .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"\" Federal defendants agree","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"DACA is unlawful , \"","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"the Justice Department said in a brief","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"filed with Judge Andrew S. Hanen in Texas ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"agreeing with the reasoning of Judge Hanen and a higher-up appeals court from several years ago","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"that the Obama administration overstepped its powers","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"by granting a categorical amnesty to potentially millions of immigrants","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"who crossed the border illegally .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"But the Justice Department said","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"it didn ' t want to see the judge issue a nationwide injunction","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"that would stop the program in its tracks ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"saying","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"the current legal situation is too messy already .","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"The move leaves it to immigrant-rights advocates and , perhaps , Democratic states , to defend the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program in what ' s likely to be the final legal showdown for the embattled program .","depth":3},{"id":20,"text":"DACA ,","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"announced by the Obama administration in 2012 ,","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"is currently protecting some 700,000 \" Dreamers \" from deportation ,","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"and offers them work permits and Social Security numbers .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"They are eligible for some taxpayer benefits .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"But the program has been controversial and legally suspect from the start","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"- President Obama repeatedly said","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"he lacked the power","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"to create such a program ,","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"before reversing himself","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"and claiming such powers .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"The Trump administration last year concluded","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"the program was , in fact , illegal ,","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"and moved to phase it out .","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"While a judge in Maryland agreed with the move ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"judges in California , New York and Washington , D.C. , said","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"the Trump administration cut too many corners","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"and the phaseout was illegal .","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"They ordered the president to restart the program , at least in terms of renewing two-year amnesties for people","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"who have been previously approved for DACA .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"Texas , meanwhile ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"which won a battle in 2015","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"to stop a broader deportation amnesty attempt by the Obama administration ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"is now demanding","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"Judge Hanen step in","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"and stop the program","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"by ruling it illegal .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"The administration ' s new brief cuts a middle ground between Texas and the pro-DACA courts .","depth":4},{"id":48,"text":"The Justice Department says","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"it agrees with Texas","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"that the program is illegal ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"but doesn ' t want the court to issue an injunction ,","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"that would create even more of a legal mess .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"\" If this court issues an injunction","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"ordering federal defendants to end the DACA policy ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"federal defendants will face simultaneous conflicting court orders","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"- which highlights the impropriety","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"of issuing nationwide injunctions as a general matter , \"","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"government lawyers said .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"They said","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"if Judge Hanen does issue an injunction ,","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"they hoped","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"he would at least grant a two-week grace period","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"so the government could rush to the Supreme Court","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"and try to get the conflicts sorted out .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"A similar request","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"made to the justices","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"was rejected earlier this year .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":137,"left":88,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":88,"left":73,"right":87,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":73,"left":70,"right":72,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":70,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":72,"left":2,"right":71,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":71,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":87,"left":86,"right":19,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":86,"left":81,"right":85,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":81,"left":77,"right":80,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":77,"left":75,"right":76,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":5,"right":74,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":74,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":76,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboratio